headlines.description: — Doug McDermott hit four 3-pointers and scored all 14 of his points in the second half and the San Antonio Spurs beat Philadelphia 114-105 on Sunday night to send the 76ers to their third straight loss to open the season.
headlines.shortLinkText: Spurs hand 76ers third straight loss to open season, 114-105

headlines.description: — Rookie Bennedict Mathurin scored 27 points, hitting three 3-pointers in a pivotal third quarter, and the Indiana Pacers beat the Detroit Pistons 124-115 on Saturday night to snap a 12-game losing streak dating to last season.
headlines.shortLinkText: Pacers ended 12-game losing streak, beating Pistons 124-115

headlines.description: — Jayson Tatum and Derrick White combined for 12 straight points late in the fourth quarter to help the Boston Celtics beat the Orlando Magic 126-120 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jayson Tatum, Derrick White lead Celtics over Magic, 126-120

headlines.description: — A scuffle inspired Toronto, and the Raptors' response forced the Miami Heat to work a little harder to secure their first win of the season.
headlines.shortLinkText: After a scuffle, Heat hold on to top Raptors 112-109

headlines.description: — No Cavaliers player had opened a season with back-to-back 30-point games, not even LeBron James, until now.
headlines.shortLinkText: Mitchell scores 32 points, Cavaliers roll past Bulls 128-96

headlines.description: — Giannis Antetokounmpo scored 44 points and became Milwaukee’s career free throws leader as the Bucks rolled to a 125-105 victory over the Houston Rockets on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Antetokounmpo scores 44 points, Bucks rout Rockets 125-105

headlines.description: — Luka Doncic dribbled behind his back before an alley-oop pass to new pick-and-roll partner Christian Wood for a one-handed dunk.
headlines.shortLinkText: Doncic, Mavs have fast start, rip Griz 137-96 in home opener

events.name: Oklahoma City Thunder at Denver Nuggets

headlines.description: — On the night the Denver Nuggets celebrated Nikola Jokic's second straight MVP trophy and their superstar tied Wilt Chamberlain for sixth all-time with his 78th triple-double, it was Jamal Murray who got the strongest hugs from his coach and biggest...
headlines.shortLinkText: Jokic, Murray lead tired Nuggets past Thunder 122-117

headlines.description: — Paul George scored 40 points to help the Los Angeles Clippers hold off the Sacramento Kings 111-109 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Paul George scores 40 as Clippers edge Kings 111-109
